Cephalopods have a couple of major hurdles to technological civilization. Firstly discovering fire is an obstacle to any aquatic organism (this is an issue for Cetaceans too). Secondly they don't raise their offspring, and have a planktonic larval phase in their life cycle which makes transmission of culture significantly more difficult since it can only occur between adults.







